Package org.opengis.wrapper.proj4

Class PJFactory.EPSG

  • Object
    • PJFactory
      • EPSG
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AuthorityFactory, CRSAuthorityFactory, Factory
    Enclosing class:
    PJFactory
    public static class PJFactory.EPSG
extends PJFactory
implements CRSAuthorityFactory
    A factory for Coordinate Reference System objects created from EPSG codes. While this factory is primarily designed for EPSG codes, it accepts also any other codespaces supported by the Proj.4 library.

    The main methods in this class are:

    • getAuthority()
    • createCoordinateReferenceSystem(String)
    The following methods delegate to createCoordinateReferenceSystem(String) and cast the result if possible, or throw a FactoryException otherwise.
    • createGeographicCRS(String)
    • createGeocentricCRS(String)
    • createProjectedCRS(String)
    • createObject(String)
    All other methods are not supported by the default implementation of this factory. However those methods will work if the createCoordinateReferenceSystem(String) method is overridden in order to return CRS objects of the appropriate type.
    Since:
    3.1

      • EPSG

        public EPSG()
        Creates a new coordinate operation factory which will create CRS with axis order as declared in the EPSG database.

      • EPSG

        public EPSG​(boolean useEpsgAxisOrder)
        Creates a new coordinate operation factory. Whether the factory will follow EPSG axis order or not is specified by the given useEpsgAxisOrder argument.
        Parameters:
        useEpsgAxisOrder - true if the CRS created by this factory should use the axis order declared by the EPSG database, or false for the Proj.4 axis order. The default value is true.

    • Method Detail

      • getAuthority

        public Citation getAuthority()
        Returns the authority for this factory, which is EPSG. This is actually the default authority when no codespace is explicitly given to a createFoo(String) method. If a codespace is explicitely given, any authority recognized by the Proj.4 library will be accepted.
        Specified by:
        getAuthority in interface AuthorityFactory

      • createCoordinateReferenceSystem

        public CoordinateReferenceSystem createCoordinateReferenceSystem​(String code)
                                                          throws FactoryException
        Creates a new CRS from the given code. If the given string is of the form "AUTHORITY:CODE", then any authority recognized by the Proj.4 library will be accepted (it doesn't need to be EPSG). If no authority is given, then "EPSG:" is assumed.
        Specified by:
        createCoordinateReferenceSystem in interface CRSAuthorityFactory
        Parameters:
        code - the code of the CRS object to create.
        Returns:
        a CRS created from the given code.
        Throws:
        FactoryException - if the CRS object can not be created for the given code.
